cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use resolver in your research or engineering work, please cite it."
title: "resolver: a Go test harness for benchmarking LLMs on agentic tool-use tasks"
abstract: >-
  resolver is a Go test harness that evaluates whether an LLM can serve as a
  resolver for agentic work in high-consequence environments — domains where
  a bad tool call, a hallucinated argument, or a missed escalation has real
  cost. The reference corpus targets sysadm-over-SSH (irreversible tools,
  destructive-request refusal, multi-step diagnostics, topology reasoning,
  escalation) but is template-not-domain-locked: adopters can re-instantiate
  the same capability tests against clinical triage, SCADA, financial
  operations, customer-service tool stacks, and similar platforms by
  swapping the system prompt, tool set, and scenario corpus while preserving
  the tier structure, regex-backed verdicts, and gated pass thresholds.
  Tier 1 runs 31 single-turn routing queries across 10 tiers with five
  gated pass/fail thresholds. Tier 2 adds multi-turn scenarios with mocked
  data-producing tools, plus meta-sweeps over tool-list size and context
  size. Scorecards are byte-exact against the RESOLVER-VALIDATION-SPEC so
  cross-model history remains comparable.
